I love Sicilian pie the best and this place makes it the best!  I haven't lived in that area for over 30 years so I have tried many different pizzerias over the years.  Recently I went on a memory lane walk through that area I grew up in.  The walk culminated by picking up one of Bad Boys Sicilian pies when I left. The neighborhood changed but the pizza was the one thing that never has. It's still just as delicious  now as it was back then!

I was told the draw to this place was their sangria and they really do have thee best sangria I've ever come across. First timer here visiting from Arizona and the service is amazing from the moment you walk in the door. Jeff the bartender was so helpful getting us a sit as soon as we walked in. The staff is so friendly and the atmosphere and service was top notch. We didn't eat much because we came for the sangria but they have this great calamari appetizer they serve with tarter sauce. I asked for marinara sauce which they didn't have but Jeff made it fresh for me at the bar and quite frankly most seafood restaurants don't even make it that well. Love this place and can't wait to visit again
